1079.question: How much does this system outperform prior work?
1079.response: {'Answer': 'The system outperforms prior work by a significant margin. On the ListOps dataset, the system achieves an accuracy of 99.2%, compared to 71.5% for the LSTM model, 60.7% for the RL-SPINN model, and 57.6% for the Gumbel Tree-LSTM model. On the SNLI dataset, the system achieves an accuracy of 84.3%, compared to 80.5% for the model by Yogatama et al. (2016), 81.6% for the model by Maillard et al. (2017), and 82.6% for the model by Choi et al. (2018). On the SST dataset, the system achieves an accuracy of 90.2%, compared to 91.8% for the model by Radford et al. (2017), 90.3% for the model by McCann et al. (2017), and 54.7% for the model by Peters et al. (2018). On the MultiNLI dataset, the system achieves an accuracy of 70.7%, compared to 69.1% for the LSTM model, 67.5% for the SPINN model, 67.4% for the RL-SPINN model, and 69.5% for the Gumbel Tree-LSTM model.'}
1079.answer: The system outperforms by 27.7% the LSTM model, 38.5% the RL-SPINN model and 41.6% the Gumbel Tree-LSTM

1080.question: What are the baseline systems that are compared against?
